Cook pasta in a large saucepan according to package directions. Add vegetables during the last 3-4 minutes of cooking. Drain. Whisk together broth, wine, flour, dill weed, garlic salt, and thyme in same saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; simmer 1 minute. Add cream; gently stir in vegetables and pasta. Cook until heated through. Garnish with Parmesan cheese if desired.